---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../lib/seo';
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy — DevKit" description="DevKit runs entirely in your browser. We don't upload, log or share your input. Read our privacy promise." path="/privacy">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-10 pb-16 prose-tool">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy</h1>
    <p>DevKit is built on three rules:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Every tool runs <strong>entirely in your browser</strong>. We do not send your input anywhere.</li>
      <li>We do not require an account, store profiles or use tracking cookies.</li>
      <li>Aggregate usage is measured with Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is cookie-less and does not see your input.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Tool input and output</h2>
    <p>
      Text pasted into formatters, encoders, decoders, generators, QR tools, Markdown preview, and similar
      utilities is processed locally in your browser. DevKit does not intentionally transmit that content
      to a server for processing.
    </p>

    <h2>What is stored locally</h2>
    <p>
      Your theme preference (dark/light) is saved in <code>localStorage</code>. You can clear it any time from your browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics and advertising</h2>
    <p>
      DevKit uses Cloudflare Web Analytics to understand aggregate traffic without tracking cookies.
      DevKit also uses Google AdSense to review the site and, when approved, serve advertising.
      Google and other advertising vendors may use cookies or similar technologies to serve ads based on
      visits to this site and other sites. These ad systems do not need your tool input to run DevKit tools.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can manage browser cookies in your browser settings. You can also control personalized advertising
      through Google's ad settings at <a class="text-accent" href="https://adssettings.google.com" rel="nofollow">adssettings.google.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Security headers and third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      We ship a Content Security Policy that limits where scripts, fonts, images, and network requests can load from.
      The policy allows the third-party services needed for analytics and advertising while keeping tool logic client-side.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy questions can be sent to
      <a class="text-accent" href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
